an class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/24/02 11:07:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=286.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which would you use?</span><hr size=1> I assume it's elemental bane damage?  If so, then it's only going to work when you're fighting elementals.  I'd go with the Dragonclaw Shard, or better yet, sell it and buy a 2 hander.  Argent protector you could probably get fairly cheap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugloynholyforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloyn Holyforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/24/02 11:23:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=286.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which would you use?</span><hr size=1> It's normally 15/20...everytime you connect there is a resist check to cold done on the mob...if passed it is THEN a functional 20/20 weapon.  But if you find yourself spending alot of time hunting Velious Mobs...ehhh.  Frankly I think the MDS is a better choice for damage, plus the neg20 Fire is pretty harsh.<br><br>Gloyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqguavus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQGuavus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/24/02 2:28:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=286.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which would you use?</span><hr size=1> I have the Dizok Imperial Katana for 2h, I should have my Defender within a week, week and a half. <br><br>Right now I'm addicted to the fast swings from the hammer/mds. They allow me to keep aggro better, in xp groups I'm usually the main tank/taunter. I have a rogue or a ranger usually, so I need the ac from the shield/1h combo while the rest of the group offs the mob.<br>We're usually hunting in Chardok, Akheva Ruins, the Hole, Maiden's Eye, the Grey, or every once in a while the pit in Velks.<br><br>Hmm, still can't decide between the two of them, it's tough.<br> <p>"Is it always the King who hangs?"- From the works of Kay<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116313" target="_blank">Guavus' profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqguavus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQGuavus</A> at: 3/24/02 2:30:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utovartrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tovar Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 1:33:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=286.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Very strange......</span><hr size=1> That you wear Scaled knight guantlets instead of Thunder Etched. I guess normal rules don't apply to some folks in Fusion.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 369